RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 14500. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 18, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CARLOS PUNCH vied for the lead, claimed the rail advantage, was joined by another competitor and set the pace in a set, rated until the quarter pole, battled with his company down the lane, matched strides, finally edged clear and held sway. Game effort. DOUBLE PRIORITY stalked the leaders from the three path, was given the cue at the three eighths pole, hand ridden through the turn, was encouraged and kept on point through the stretch drive, slowly but surely gained ground, did not have enough time or room to catch the winner but was second best today. MY HEAVY SON was off a bit slow, found his stride and starting advancing before the half, improved position and angled out six wide at the three eighths pole, circled the field in the turn was in contention by the quarter pole, was driven down the land in the five path passing rivals and was able to get up for show. ONE TOUGH CHARLIE vied for the lead, settled next to the other front runner and led in as set, rated together until the three eighths pole, was given the cue and encouraged to pick it up through the turn, did not make any advantage but stayed with the other front runner, battled down the stretch, gave way in the last sixteenth of a mile. HEREWECOMETOGETYOU was off a tad bit slow, raved four wide down the back side, improved position through the turn, had no late kick. OSCAR CHOICE raced two wide while saving ground on the inside, raced with another rival to his outside, had a clean trip but made no impact. SILKY'S DANCE was pinched a bit at the start, raced three wide early, improved position and was in contention by the quarter pole, tried to close in on the field but to no avial. HALF A BUCK rail, was never involved.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 11000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.

MR. BUTCH WOMBLE stalked the front runner, advanced up the rail, drew next to the early leader and led in set with that rival, this set was challenged and joined by another set of outside stalkers at the five sixteenth pole,, MR. BUTCH WOMBLE was able to get the lead at the quarter pole, was driven down the lane but drifted out badly and just missed. LIFEASWEKNOWIT stalked from the four path, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, angled into the two path and saved ground, gained ground leaving the turn and closed into the third place. ALLIGATOR CRAWL raced on the rail, was off of the pace, saved ground, advanced into contention, struggled to switch leads and tired late. DEPART raced along the rail while trailing the field early on, advanced along the rail and shifted into the three path at the three eighths pole, entered the stretch under heavy encouragement and in the three path, closed down the stretch with a good turn of foot and passed rivals. MESABI raced from th emiddle of the pack on the outside in the six path, shifted out in the turn and was ten side in the stretch. EL MONGO was sent for the early lead, set the pace for the first fraction, in the three path, was joined by an inside rival and set the second set of fractions in a set, ws pressured by outside closer and began to give way in the lane, drifted out in the stretch. SHAKEDOWN STREET was stalking the front runners from the outside and in the six path,, joined another competitor and raced in a set through the turn, challenged for the lead at the five sixteenth pole, tired late. RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 6 5F Dirt CR: 87. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MARCH 18, 2023. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DIAL IN FOR LUTE raced mid pack along the rail, advanced up the fence at the half mile pole, shifted out into the six path at the five sixteenth pole, was asked and responded well closing ground down the lane, shifted into the four and three path while drawing off for the win. BIBLEMAN was five wide, vied for the early lead, settled off the pace and stalked the leader, stayed within stalking distance of the lead, launched a bid at the quarter pole, responded well to urging and encouragement, collared the leader after the sixteenth pole, briefly led the race, was caught by a fast closing late and just missed. TWO DOT was pinched at the stat, raced three wide, advanced at the half mile pole, shifted out nearing the three eighths pole, circled the field in the turn, shifted six wide in the upper stretch, closed with determination, was able to walk away with third. GLENN'S JUMPER vied for the early lead, set the pace while racing along the rail, tired at the eighth pole. SHARK HARBOR vied for the lead, raced three wide, was joined by an outside rival, stalked in a set until the quarter pole then tired. WONDER RUN raced well off the pace in the four path, maintained that position through out and h ad no late kick. TRIPPER JOHN was five wide and stalking the front runners, shuffled back and raced mid pack, followed the eventual winner through the turn but to no avail. HALFMOON REEF was sharp out of the gates, had the rail, quickly began to fade. CAYMANS COBRA was off slow and showed little. CAYMANS COBRA WAS PULLED UP IN THE MIDDLE OF THE STRETCH AND WALKED OF.
